Name: Ellen C. Babbitt
Title: Ellen C. Babbitt file
Description: File documenting the participation of Ellen Babbitt in World War I. Babbitt entered the Red Cross in March 1918. She served in the Children's Bureau in Washington, D.C., Lyon, Marsaille, and Paris in France, and in England and Scotland, working on children's welfare education. File includes service record card, photograph of Babbitt, newspaper clipping, and two letters, including a personal letter from Babbitt to Ange Milner.
Related organization/service branch: American National Red Cross; American National Red Cross. Children's Bureau

Name: Mabel L. Morgan
Title: Mabel L. Morgan file
Description: File documenting the participation of Mabel L. Morgan in World War I. Morgan volunteered on November 3, 1917, in the Army Nurse Corps and received training at Camp Grant, Illinois. She transferred to Fort Sill, Oklahoma, on January 26, 1918. On November 9, 1918, she was sent to Hoboken, New Jersey, where she was prepared to leave for France with Base Hospital #90, but the armistice was signed. She stayed at a hospital in the area until April 13, 1919. File includes a Morgan's service record card, letters, and an RSVP card.
Related organization/service branch: United States. Army Nurse Corps
Topics: Morgan, Mabel L.; World War, 1914-1918; Illinois State Normal University--Students

Name: Elizabeth Ellen O'Keefe
Title: Elizabeth Ellen O'Keefe file
Description: File documenting the participation of Elizabeth Ellen O'Keefe in World War I. O'Keefe entered the service on February 18, 1918, in the Army Nurse Corps in the Red Cross. She was first stationed at Camp Custer, Michigan, and was transferred to New York City to join Base Hospital no. 14. She was sent overseas on July 14, 1918, and was stationed at Mars-sur-Allier, France. She became the chief nurse at U.S. Convalescent Hospital no. 4 in Nice, France. O'Keefe returned to the States on July 31, 1919, and was discharged on August 31, 1918. Description supplemented by information from Fold3.
Related organization/service branch: United States. Army Nurse Corps; American National Red Cross
Topics: O'Keefe, Elizabeth Ellen; World War, 1914-1918; Illinois State Normal University--Students

Description: File documents the participation of Alice Orme Smith in World War I. Smith entered the army on May 14, 1917, and served with the Presbyterian Base Hospital Unit no. 2. Name: Charlotte Lois Smith
Title: Charlotte Lois Smith file
Description: File documenting the participation of Charlotte Lois Smith in World War I. Smith enlisted in August 1918, and served in the Medical Department in the Army. Name: Julia Scott Vrooman
Title: Julia Scott Vrooman file
Description: File documenting the participation of Julia Scott Vrooman in World War I. Vrooman joined the entertainment division of the Y.M.C.A. on August 23, 1918. She was sent overseas with her husband upon entering the service and was stationed in Paris, France. She organized the jazz band for the Y.M.C.A. After the armistice was signed, she was stationed in Mayen, Germany. She returned to the States on September 12, 1919, and was released from service the same day. File includes a survey, Vrooman's service record card, photos, a letter, newspaper clippings, and a booklet she wrote.
Related organization/service branch: YMCA of the USA

Name: Flavia Williams
Title: Flavia Williams file
Description: File documenting the participation of Flavia Williams in World War I. Williams entered the service on May 1, 1919, and was a nurse's aide in the Red Cross. She sailed to Siberia on May 10, 1919. She was stationed at Irkutsk, Siberia, and then transferred to Verkhne-Udinsk, Siberia, (renamed Ulan-Ude in 1934) on September 5, 1919. She returned to Irkutsk on October 25, 1919. Williams left for the States on February 5, 1920, and was discharged on February 20, 1920. File includes a survey, William's service record card, a receipt for mailing an insured package, letters, a note from William's mother documenting letters she has received from her, and a newspaper clipping. Description supplemented by information from Fold3.
Related organization/service branch: American National Red Cross
